      "description": "After flipping a cell, the DP values (R and D) are only recomputed along the main diagonal (r+1, c+1). However, a change in a cell can affect cells to its right and below, not just the diagonal ones. This leads to an incorrect total count of staircases after updates.",
      "triggering_input": "2 2 1\n1 1\n",
      "fix": "When a cell (x, y) is toggled, recompute DP values for the entire sub‑matrix of cells with row ≥ x and column ≥ y in the correct order (e.g., row‑major). For each cell (i, j) in that region, recompute R[i][j] = 0 if locked else 1 + (D[i][j-1] if j>1 else 0) and D[i][j] = 0 if locked else 1 + (R[i-1][j] if i>1 else 0). Update the total by subtracting the old contribution (R+ D-1 for free cells, 0 for locked) and adding the new contribution. This ensures all dependent cells are updated and the total remains correct.",
      "confirmed": true,
      "reasoning": "The original code only updates cells (r, c), (r+1, c+1), (r+2, c+2), … . A toggle at (1,1) in a 2×2 grid should reduce the total from 10 to 5, but the code only subtracts 1, giving 9. The missing propagation to cells (1,2), (2,1) and (2,2) causes the error. Recomputing the whole affected sub‑matrix fixes the propagation and yields the correct result."
